# Cursor Rules for Recall Project

## Code Style & Formatting
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Follow ESLint and Prettier configurations
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add JSDoc comments for APIs

## UI
- Mobile first web design
- Always reach for a shadcn component when available
- Keep everything as simple and vanilla shadncn as possible.

## Project Structure
- Keep components in `/components` directory
- Store utilities in `/utils` directory
- Place types/interfaces in `/types` directory
- Use index files for clean imports

## Best Practices
- Prefer functional components over class components
- Use React hooks for state management
- Implement proper error handling
- Write unit tests for new features

## Dependencies
- Prefer established, well-maintained packages
- Keep dependencies up to date
- Document any new dependencies in README

## Performance
- Optimize for mobile performance
- Use lazy loading where appropriate
- Minimize bundle size
- Implement proper caching strategies
